"][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section parallax="false" bg_image="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Green_back_03.jpg" bg_color="#449322" class="call_to_action" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 45px 0px 45px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text class="nomargin" style="margin: 0!important;"]<h4 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">Get A Free Quote</span></h4>[/x_text][gravityform id="4" title="false" description="false" ajax="true"][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text class="left-text "]In need of high-quality tree and shrubbery services in the Toronto area? <a href="https://www.almileytree.com/contact-us/" title="Contact Us" target="_blank">Get in touch</a> with us today to begin benefitting from our fully insured team of expert arborists. We can further inform you on our services, possible solutions to your plant-related problems, and we can even provide a free estimate![/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/3"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_gap size="50px"][x_image type="none" src="https://www.almileytree.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/home-2.jpg" alt="Tree Service" link="false" href="#" title="" target="" info="none" info_place="right" info_trigger="hover" info_content="" id="free_label" style="width: 100%; margin: -49px auto 0 auto; min-height: 180px;"][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#ffffff" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 70px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Tree Removal Mississauga[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]<p>Preserving plant life at all cost is the noble thing to do. There, however, comes a time when removing a tree from your property is the best way to go. Often times, tree removal is considered so as to clear the ground needed for a construction. Other times, a tree is removed because it is dying. If your tree is beyond restoration and is dying because it has come to the end of its life, tree removal will be warranted.</p>
<h4>What makes tree removal necessary?</h4>
<ul>
<li>Incurable diseases</li>
<li>Extreme weather damage</li>
<li>Pollution</li>
<li>Soil compaction</li>
<li>Damage from human activity or interaction</li>
<li>Tree posing risk to surrounding properties</li>
</ul>
<p>With us, tree removal in Mississauga is only considered as a last resort. The two main reasons that permit a tree removal are when the tree is beyond restoration and when the health of the tree risks the safety of people and properties around it. We believe that tree removal should only be done by skilled experts.</p>
<p>Do you feel the tree on your property poses risk to you and your buildings? Give us a call today for a professional inspection. If tree removal is warranted, we will help with that. At Al Miley & Associates we have the resources needed to thoroughly inspect and safely remove a tree, regardless of its size, from your property</p>[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Tree Protection Mississauga[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]Just like all living things, plants do get sick and they require a trusted tree doctor to monitor and administer the best treatment. Trees are prone to innumerable diseases and pests. Some of the pests and diseases are specific to certain species. While some problems require immediate tree removal, most tree problems can be treated.
Â 
The first step in tree treatment is identifying the cause of the problem. <a title="Al Miley & Associates" href="https://www.almileytree.com/">Al Miley & Associates</a> works with experienced and highly trained arborists who are can diagnose virtually any tree problem and give the best treatment. Our arborists are required to take continuous training to enhance their skills. Whether all that is needed is pest control, selective pruning or tree removal, our certified arborists in Mississauga will give you the best solution for your tree issue.
Â 
With us, you can always count on personalized approaches to tree health care. We donâ€™t just treat the visible symptoms. We consider the regional pests, local weather, regional diseases and the overall condition of your landscape before recommending a treatment plan. Talk to us today for a free inspection and recommendations on treatment.[/x_text][x_gap size="30px"][x_button   size="x-large" block="false" circle="false" icon_only="false" href="https://www.almileytree.com/contact-us/" title="" target="blank" info="none" info_place="top" info_trigger="hover" info_content=""]Get Free Estimate  [x_icon type="arrow-right"][/x_button][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 70px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Tree Pruning Mississauga[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]<p>Professional pruning will make your trees look aesthetically attractive and healthy. Regular pruning is advised for property owners who want to have trees and shrubs that have a great shape and are aesthetically pleasing. There are three benefits that come with professional pruning.</p>
<h4>Health</h4>
<p>Regular pruning will boost the overall health of your trees. This is achieved by boosting air circulation and sunlight penetration. Well-pruned plants are also less prone to pest infestations. Healthier plants live longer and look better.</p>
<h4>Safety</h4>
<p>Fallen tree limbs can be hazardous to people, buildings and the landscape. Pruning creates a safer environment by removing broken, dead and weak limbs. Removing the hazardous limbs will reduce the risk of accidents as well as damage to property.</p>
<h4>Manicured landscape</h4>
<p>Aesthetics are the immediate benefits of professional pruning services in Mississauga. Shrubbery and branches that have been pruned by a professional will create for you a landscape that you admire. Businesses will also benefit from the service by enhancing the brand image through the natural scenery. A positive atmosphere is created with professionally pruned trees and shrubs.</p>
<p>We work with a fully certified team of arborists who will help with all your pruning needs in the Mississauga community. Give us a call today.</p>[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Tree Arborists  Mississauga[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][x_text class="left-text "]<p>To keep the trees and shrubs on your property as visually attractive and healthy as can be, you need professional trimming services. Al Miley & Associates is the go-to company in matters expert trimming services in Mississauga. Our company offers a combination of services to create and maintain a well-manicured yard. In addition to tree trimming, our services include stump removal, tree cutting, pruning, and storm cleanup. Our team has an eye for detail and will leave your yard looking as immaculate as can be.</p>
<p>Our expert tree trimming services will help with the following:</p>
<h4>Improved safety</h4>
<p>Unkempt trees are bound to have broken and weak limbs. These pose a risk to buildings and people when they fall off. Gusts of winds are the main causes of weak or broken limbs. Our team takes safety very seriously and will ensure your trees have no hazardous limbs.</p>
<h4>Facilitate tree development</h4>
<p>To achieve a healthy growth, the weak and diseased limbs need to be removed. Doing so will allow the trees to heal. To promote healthy tree development, we will help with the removal of dead and weak limbs and also thin out branches. This will promote the much needed air circulation and sunlight penetration.</p>
<h4>Aesthetics</h4>
<p>Making your yard look bright is our primary focus. We achieve this with expertly shaped shrubs and trees. Our team is good at creating harmonious designs.</p>[/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#ffffff" id="section-whyUs" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 25px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="center-text "]Tree Restoration Mississauga[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_text]<p>Al Miley & Associates specializes in tree restoration in Mississauga and the Greater Toronto Area community. Whether you want to save a dying tree or to spruce things up, we have you covered. We are a certified team of arborists in Missisauga with a high regard for plant life.</p>
<h4>Factors that affect the health of a tree</h4>

<ul>
<li>Pollution</li>
<li>Soil compaction</li>
<li>Storm damage</li>
<li>Diseases</li>
<li>Damage by human activities or interaction</li>
</ul>
<p>Trees in urban areas experience more exposure and are hence more prone. Call us for a restoration.</p>[/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 10px auto 10px auto; padding: 10px 0px 0p20px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  class="left-text " style="padding: 1px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Inspection[/x_custom_headline][x_text]You cannot treat what you donâ€™t know. Our work starts with an inspection which is aimed at identifying the cause of a tree problem. Tree removal is only considered when there is no other viable option.Â Â We are committed to restoring trees to their glory by combining a range of arborist practices and techniques. It is only after determining that a tree cannot be redeemed or if it is a hazard to its surrounding that we opt for tree removal.[/x_text][/x_column][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  style="padding: 0px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h3" accent="false"]Fertilizers[/x_custom_headline][x_text]Plants cannot thrive on what they get from the soil. Most of the essential nutrients need to be supplemented. We supply special fertilizers that are unique to your specific tree in order to replenish the food source of your tree and promote optimal nutrient absorption. Our fertilizers will help your trees achieve maximum health benefits.
Â [/x_text][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#f7f9d2" id="section-services" class="center-text " style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 70px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="man"]Tree Cabling and Bracing Mississauga[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="20px"][x_text class="justify-text "]Given the right conditions, any tree can experience the un-rooted problem. The main sign of this problem is the tree bending awkwardly in one direction. Al Miley & Associates have handled many problems related to un-rooting and we offer advanced services in cabling and bracing. Our service will leave your tree standing upright, safer and healthier.[/x_text][x_gap size="20px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_feature_list animation_offset="50" animation_delay_initial="0" animation_delay_between="170"][x_feature_box title="When to use cabling and bracing" title_color="" text="Bad weather and the weak innate structure of a tree are the main reasons why the cabling and bracing systems have become popular. Trees in areas prone to storms and high winds and trees with a weak inherent structure are prone to un-rooting. Cabling and bracing offers the support a tree needs to stand upright. The system is also recommended for trees that are prone to the splitting problem. The system can also be used to strengthen weak branches." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="100px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#095c31" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="clock-o" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Â  Risk and damage" title_color="" text="Unrooted trees are at a high risk of falling and they can damage buildings and the landscape. Cabling and bracing can help prevent this risk.Â 
Â " text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="100px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#634f40" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="unlink" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][x_feature_box title="Â  Additional expense" title_color="" text="Once a tree is unrooted, you will have to spend money filling the divot in the yard and also prepare for removing and disposing the fallen tree. Fallen trees will also block paths/roads." text_color="" graphic="icon" graphic_size="100px" graphic_shape="circle" graphic_color="#65ac22" graphic_bg_color="" align_h="left" align_v="top" side_graphic_spacing="0px" max_width="none" child="true" connector_width="0px" connector_style="solid" connector_color="" graphic_icon="dollar" graphic_animation="jello" connector_animation="jello"][/x_feature_list][/x_column][/x_row][/x_section][x_section bg_color="#ffffff" id="section-whyUs" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 25px 0px; "][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 0px auto 0px auto; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/1"  style="padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; "][x_custom_headline level="h2" looks_like="h2" accent="true" class="center-text "]Why Choose Us?[/x_custom_headline][x_gap size="30px"][/x_column][/x_row][x_row inner_container="true" marginless_columns="false" bg_color="" style="margin: 10px auto 10px auto; padding: 10px 0px 0p20px 0px; "][x_column bg_color="" type="1/2"  class="left-text " style="padding: 1px 1px 1px 1px; "][x_feature_list][x_feature_box title="The Arborist Advantage" title_color="" text="While you donâ€™t need to hire an arborist to help with allÂ treeÂ issues, some problems require that you hire an expert. Different plant species are prone to unique problems and require specialized handling.
